layer.title: Overarching goals
layer.annotation: Goal: Build GNU's latest source distribution of Guile and test it. Tool: Alpine Linux. Subtool: Busybox shell Result: successResult
Goal: Dump this shell's history to the terminal and a file at the path "/herstory" Tool: Alpine Linux. Subtool: Busybox shell Result: successResult

layer.title: Subgoals
layer.annotation: Goal: Download and extract the latest Guile source distribution from GNU's online archive in the current user's home directory. Tool: cd command (built into Busybox's shell) Tool: GNU wget Tool: tar (built into the Busybox multi-call binary) Result: successResult

Goal: Descend into the extracted Guile source distribution directory then build and install Guile. Tool: `cd` command (built into Busybox's shell) Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running Guile's `configure` script and Alpine's `setup-apkrepos` scripts. Tool: ls (built into the Busybox multi-call binary) Tool: Alpine `apk` package management command. Tool: GNU's `make` command. Result: successResult
Goal: Test newly-installed Guile interpreter. Tool: Guile's REPL shell invoked using the `guile` command. Result: successResult

layer.title: Individual commands
layer.annotation: Goal: Change working directory to the current user's home directory. Tool: cd command (built into Busybox's shell) Result: successResult

Goal: Download the latest release of the Guile source distribution from GNU's public archive server. Mistakes: `tar ` is reflexively typed before the operator realizes that they must download the archive before extracting it. Result: successResult
Goal: Extract the newly-downloaded, Guile source distribution archive. Tool: tar (built into the Busybox multi-call binary) Result: successResult
Goal: Descend into the newly-extracted Guile source distribution directory. Tool: cd command (built into Busybox's shell) Result: successResult
Goal: Obtain a directory listing of the current working directory (the base of the downloaded Guile source distribution) Tool: ls (built into the Busybox multi-call binary) Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the build system for Guile so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running Guile's `configure` script. Discoveries: A working C compiler must be installed before Guile can be built. Result: successFailure

Goal: Pick an Alpine mirror for the `apk` package manager to use, and enable the community repository. Tools: Busybox's built-in Borne shell interpreter runs Alpine's `setup-apkrepos` script. Mistake: `apk ` is typed before the operator realizes their mistake and types `setup-apkrepos` instead. Result: successResult

Goal: Install the GNU C Compiler and the standard C library headers for the running Musl libC. Tool: The `apk` command's `add` subcommand Mistake: The user begins typing the `./configure` command before realizing that additional packages need to be installed first. Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the build system for Guile so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running Guile's `configure` script. Discoveries: The headers for the GNU Multiple Precision Arithmetic Library must be installed before Guile can be built. Result: successFailure

Goal: Install the GNU Multiple Precision Library. Tool: The Alpine `apk` package manager. Discovery: The GNU Multiple Precision Library appears to already be installed. Mistakes: The operator forgets to install the development headers for GMP. Result: successResult
Goal: Search for GMP packages in the Alpine package lists. Tool: The `apk` package manager's `search` subcommand. Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the build system for Guile so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running Guile's `configure` script. Discoveries: The headers for the GNU Multiple Precision Arithmetic Library must be installed before Guile can be built. Result: successFailure

Goal: Configure the build system for Guile so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running Guile's `configure` script. Discoveries: The operator realizes that they didn't install the `-dev` headers for GMP while configure is running with the `--enable-mini-gmp` flag. They realize this and interrupt the `./configure` command.. Result: successUnknown
Goal: Search for GMP packages in the Alpine package lists. Tool: The `apk` package manager's `search` subcommand. Result: successResult

Goal: Install the development headers for the GNU Multiple Precision Library. Tool: The Alpine `apk` package manager. Discovery: The GNU Multiple Precision Library appears to already be installed. Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the build system for Guile so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running Guile's `configure` script. Discoveries: The GNU `libunistring` library is required for Guile to build. Result: successFailure
Goal: Search for Alpine packages matching the string `unistring`. Tool: The `apk` package manager's `search` subcommand. Result: successResult

Goal: Install the GNU `libunistring` package for Alpine. Tool: Alpine's `apk` package manager's `add` subcommand Mistakes: Operator starts to type `libini` but corrects the mistake. Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the build system for Guile so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running Guile's `configure` script. Discoveries: The `libffi` library is required for Guile to build. Result: successFailure
Goal: Search for Alpine packages related to the string `libffi`. Tool: Alpine's `apk` package management tool's `search` Result: successResult
Goal: Install the `libffi-dev` Alpine package. Tool: Alpine's `apk`'s `add` operation Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the build system for Guile so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running Guile's `configure` script. Discoveries: The `bdw-gc` library is required for Guile to build. Result: successFailure
Goal: Search for Alpine packages related to the string `bdw-gc`. Tool: Alpine's `apk` package management tool's `search` Result: successResult
Goal: Install the `gc-dev` package from an Alpine archive mirror. Tool: Alpine's `apk`'s `add` subcommand Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the build system for Guile so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running Guile's `configure` script. Discoveries: GNU make is required for Guile to build. Result: successFailure
Goal: Install the GNU `make` package from an Alpine archive mirror. Tool: Alpine's `apk`'s `add` operation Result: successResult

Configure the build system for Guile so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running Guile's `configure` script. Mistake: Operator begins to type `g+` at the beginning of their command line before clearing the command line and typing again. Result: successResult
Goal: Build the newly-configured Guile sources from the Guild source distribution. Tool: GNU `make` running the default target for the project. Result: successResult

Goal: Install Guile to the `configure`d `PREFIX`. Tool: GNU `make` running the `install` target. Mistake: Typed the letter `n` one too many times in `install` before catching the typo and removing the extra letter. Result: successResult
Goal: Test the Guile installation's ability to evaluate and run Guile scheme. Tool: Guile's interactive REPL shell invoked via the `guile` command. Result: successResult
Goal: Dump this shell's history to the terminal and a file at the path "/herstory" Tool: Alpine Linux. Subtool: Result: successResult

layer.title: Guile REPL shell
layer.annotation: Goal: Print the string `Lookie, Julia!` to the terminal. Tool: The `display` function built into the default Guile installation. Mistake: Operator forgets to add a comma in the string they're typing into their `display` call. Discovery: The `display` function in Scheme does not append a `newline`. Result: successResult

Goal: Print the string `Always scheming` followed by a `newline` to the terminal. Tool: The `display` function built into Scheme. Tool: The `newline` function built into Scheme. Mistakes: Operator pressed a cursor key on their keyboard by mistake, leading to extra garbage printed in the terminal that they clean up. Later on, while typing the rest of the Scheme, the operator adds an extra space and the wrong parenthesis (` (` when they meant to type `)`), which the operator fixes. Result: successResult
Goal: Exit the Guile REPL shell. Tool: The EOF control character sent by the operator pressing `Ctrl`+`D` on their keyboard. Result: successResult
